title.narrative: 1.4. HIV/AIDS PREVENTION

description.narrative: Output 1.4: By 2021, the capacity of MOHME and other relevant partners is enhanced to provide quality HIV/AIDS preventive measures through the Prevention of Mother to Child Transmission of HIV (PMTCT) and ALL IN (with emphasis on most high risk adolescents) services with specific focus on marginalized population., which contributes to Adolescents And Hiv/Aids, Evaluation, Fast-Track The End Of Hiv/Aids, Fast-Track The End Of Hiv/Aids (Covid), Learning, Skills, Participation And Engagement, Pmtct And Infant Male Circumcision, Research. UNICEF aims to achieve this through Advocacy And Communications, Advocacy And Public Engagement, Community Engagement, Social And Behaviour Change, Data, Research, Evaluation And Knowledge Management, Evaluations, Research And Data, Fostering Innovation And Use Of New Technologies, Innovation, Systems Strengthening And Institution Building, Systems Strengthening To Leave No One Behind, United Nations Working Together. This contributes to the following Country Programme result: Outcome 1: By the end of 2021, children, adolescents and mothers use improved and equitable high-impact health, nutrition and HIV/AIDS services, with a specific focus on prevention of NCD risk factors
